To ensure computational efficiency during online training, we estimate the dataset quality by randomly sampling a subset $\hat{d} \subset d$.
Let $\bar{s}(\hat{d})$ be the average instance score over this sampled subset. We define the final recipe reward $\mathcal{R}(r)$ by incorporating penalties for execution failures:
\begin{equation}
\mathcal{R}(r) = \begin{cases}
    -\lambda_{\emptyset}, & \text{if}\ d = \emptyset ,\\
    -\lambda_{\mathrm{fmt}}, & \text{if}\ d\ \text{\small{violates training format}}, \\
    \bar{s}(\hat{d}), & \text{\small{otherwise}},
\end{cases}
这是 method 部分的一个 reward 设计，我需要加入一个 d = \emptyset 的声明：大部分是因为 code failure

这是一个非常关键的补充，能够体现您对实验细节的把控（即您知道为什么数据会是空的）。

要在 Method 部分自然地加入“$d=\emptyset$ 主要是因为 code failure”这一说明，有三种常用的顶会（NeurIPS/ICLR/ICML）写法。

### 方案 1：在正文中解释（最推荐，逻辑最顺畅）
这种写法在引出公式前就说明了 $d=\emptyset$ 的物理含义，让读者在看公式时立刻明白为什么要惩罚这一项。

\noindent
\textbf{Refined Text:}
To ensure computational efficiency during online training, we estimate dataset quality using a random subset $\hat{d} \subset d$. Let $\bar{s}(\hat{d})$ denote the mean instance score of this subset. 
We define the final recipe reward $\mathcal{R}(r)$ by incorporating penalties for **synthesis failures (typically stemming from code execution errors)** and format violations:
\begin{equation}
\mathcal{R}(r) = \begin{cases}
    -\lambda_{\emptyset}, & \text{if}\ d = \emptyset \quad \text{\small{(execution failure)}}, \\
    -\lambda_{\mathrm{fmt}}, & \text{if}\ d\ \text{\small{violates format}}, \\
    \bar{s}(\hat{d}), & \text{\small{otherwise}},
\end{cases}
\end{equation}

---

### 方案 2：在公式后的 Where 语句中解释（最严谨）
这种写法符合数学定义的规范，保持了正文的简洁，把具体的工程细节（code failure）放在定义的补充说明中。

\noindent
\textbf{Refined Text:}
...
We define the final recipe reward $\mathcal{R}(r)$ as follows:
\begin{equation}
\mathcal{R}(r) = \begin{cases}
    -\lambda_{\emptyset}, & \text{if}\ d = \emptyset, \\
    -\lambda_{\mathrm{fmt}}, & \text{if}\ d\ \text{\small{violates training format}}, \\
    \bar{s}(\hat{d}), & \text{\small{otherwise}},
\end{cases}
\end{equation}
where $\lambda_{\emptyset}$ and $\lambda_{\mathrm{fmt}}$ represent penalties for empty datasets and formatting errors, respectively. **Note that $d = \emptyset$ primarily indicates code execution failures** where the recipe fails to generate valid instances.

---

### 方案 3：直接写在 Case 条件里（最直观）
如果您的公式行宽允许，直接写在条件里是让读者一眼看懂的最快方式。

\noindent
\textbf{Refined Text:}
...
We define the final recipe reward $\mathcal{R}(r)$ to penalize invalid outcomes:
\begin{equation}
\mathcal{R}(r) = \begin{cases}
    -\lambda_{\emptyset}, & \text{if}\ d = \emptyset \ \text{\small{(mostly due to code failure)}}, \\
    -\lambda_{\mathrm{fmt}}, & \text{if}\ d\ \text{\small{violates training format}}, \\
    \bar{s}(\hat{d}), & \text{\small{otherwise}},
\end{cases}
\end{equation}

---

### 润色建议：
1.  **"Code failure" 的学术化表达：** 
    建议使用 **"code execution failure"** 或 **"synthesis execution error"**，显得更精准。
2.  **"Estimate" 的表达：**
    第一句中的 "estimate the dataset quality" 可以改为 **"approximate the dataset quality"**，听起来更数学化。
3.  **符号的一致性：**
    我在方案 1 中把 "violates training format" 稍微缩短了一点，以防公式太宽。

### 综合推荐（直接复制版）
结合了方案 1 的流畅和方案 2 的严谨：

To ensure computational efficiency during online training, we approximate the dataset quality by randomly sampling a subset $\hat{d} \subset d$.
Let $\bar{s}(\hat{d})$ be the average instance score over this subset. We define the recipe reward $\mathcal{R}(r)$ to penalize validity issues, specifically **empty datasets (typically caused by code execution failures)** and format violations:
\begin{equation}
\mathcal{R}(r) = \begin{cases}
    -\lambda_{\emptyset}, & \text{if}\ d = \emptyset, \\
    -\lambda_{\mathrm{fmt}}, & \text{if}\ d\ \text{\small{violates training format}}, \\
    \bar{s}(\hat{d}), & \text{\small{otherwise}}.
\end{cases}
\end{equation}

